jobInfo.title: Human Resources Manager
jobInfo.desc:
• Executes, controls, and coordinates the human resources functional needs and workplace relations based activities within a segment or business unit
  • Implements, monitors, reviews, and evaluates human resources management strategies, policies, and plans to meet business needs and ensures compliance with employee related regulatory requirements
  • Ensures sound recruitment and selection practices, appropriate on-boarding, induction, socialization, training, and development programs
  • Implements performance management systems to plan, appraise, and improve individual and team performance
  • Represents organization in negotiations with unions and employees to determine compensation and other conditions of employment

Job Category: First/Mid-level Manager/Supervisor oversees and directs the delivery of products, services or functions through the work of subordinate employees, implements policies, programs and directives set by the organization's executives, and is responsible for pay determination, hire and termination decisions, and performance reviews.
